# Frontend conventions

## Vue SFC

- `<script setup lang="ts">` only. Block order: template → script → style.
- Single quotes in templates and scripts. 4-space indent. Semicolons required.
- `defineProps<{...}>()` and `defineEmits<{...}>()` with TS interfaces.
- Explicit function return types everywhere (ESLint enforced).
- Type imports: `import type { Foo } from '~/types'` (separate type imports).
- Add `data-testid` to interactive elements for E2E targeting.

## Routing

Routes live in `frontend/modules/`, NOT `pages/`. Each route is an `index.vue`. Colocation folders (`components/`, `composables/`, `types/`, `utils/`) next to pages are ignored by the router.

## State

Use `useState` in composables (e.g. `useAuth`, `useApi`). No Pinia.

## Shared components

Place in `frontend/components/` (auto-imported, `pathPrefix: false`). Page-scoped components go in `components/` next to the page's `index.vue`.

## Styling

Tailwind utility classes via Nuxt UI. Custom palettes: `komm`, `sand`. Font: Poppins. Avoid custom CSS unless for safe-area/mobile-shell layouts.

## Lint

Run `npm run lint` from `frontend/` or root. ESLint flat config enforces all style rules.
